hopobject.body: How much notice do you have to give? webmd fluticasone propionate The article says “irradiated water”. Actually it is “contaminated water”. Irradiated refers to water exposed to radiation, which does not make the water itself radioactive. Radioactive particles would normally be contained inside the fuel rods. What they have is water contaminated with very radioactive material from broken fuel rods. Such as uranium, plutonium, cesium, strontium, iodine, xenon, etc. I recommend following enenews DOT com.
